sentence: GMS Inc.GMS was a big mover last session, as the company saw its shares rise more than 5% on the day.
The move came on solid volume too with far more shares changing hands than in a normal session.
This continues the recent uptrend for the company as the stock is now up 11.6% in the past one-month time frame.
The move came after the company reported solid first-quarter fiscal 2018 results.

The company has seen three negative estimate revisions in the past few months, while its Zacks Consensus Estimate for the current quarter has also moved lower over the past few months, suggesting there may be trouble down the road.
So make sure to keep an eye on this stock going forward, to see if this recent move higher can last.
GMS Inc. currently has a Zacks Rank #3 (Hold) while its Earnings ESP is 0.00%.
